<!-- content block h/h -->
<div class="c_block halved" data-anchor="wellbeing" data-float-col="light">
        <div class="content">
        <div class="inner">
                        <h1>Wellbeing</h1>
            <p>Our Wellbeing curriculum is guided by our Catholic identity and aims to equip students with the knowledge and understanding they need to promote their own welfare and that of others. Our Wellbeing curriculum is aligned to the Victorian Curriculum, teaching Personal and Social Capabilities. It is designed to teach important skills as they relate to our three key wellbeing areas: Relationships, Relevance, and Resilience.</p>
<p><a href="https://sfx.vic.edu.au/curriculum/wellbeing/">Learn More</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>
            <div class="image" style="background-image:url(https://sfx.vic.edu.au/cms/content/uploads/2023/01/home_wellbeing-e1674619954667-1.png)"></div>
    </div>
<!-- end content block h/h -->


<!-- content block h/h -->
<div class="c_block halved" data-anchor="junior" data-float-col="dark">
            <div class="image" style="background-image:url(https://sfx.vic.edu.au/cms/content/uploads/2023/04/Junior-scaled-e1681747501830-930x930.jpg)"></div>
        <div class="content">
        <div class="inner">
                        <h1>Junior</h1>
            <p>Our Junior Curriculum sets a strong foundation in a variety of learning disciplines, providing students the opportunity to build skills and pursue interests with an eye to future studies. In Years 7 to 9, students are introduced to subjects across all areas of the curriculum, giving them a breadth of learning before they filter down into the specific areas they aim to pursue in their lives after school. Students are supported with specialist facilities, vibrant events and elective choices to help them tailor their education.</p>
<p><a href="https://sfx.vic.edu.au/curriculum/">Curriculum</a>  <a href="https://sfx.vic.edu.au/campus/berwick/">Berwick</a>  <a href="https://sfx.vic.edu.au/campus/officer/">Officer</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>
    </div>
<!-- end content block h/h -->


<!-- content block h/h -->
<div class="c_block halved" data-anchor="senior" data-float-col="light">
        <div class="content">
        <div class="inner">
                        <h1>Senior</h1>
            <p>Our Senior Curriculum prepares students for the final stage of their secondary education and life after school, with a choice of academic and vocational pathways to suit their needs. Students are able to complete their schooling with the VCE, VCE VM, or a number of other programs, all designed to suit different needs and prepare students for post-school pathways. Senior students are supported with a positive school community, accelerated learning opportunities and speciality subjects.</p>
<p><a href="https://sfx.vic.edu.au/curriculum/">Curriculum</a>  <a href="https://sfx.vic.edu.au/campus/beaconsfield/">Beaconsfield</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>
            <div class="image" style="background-image:url(https://sfx.vic.edu.au/cms/content/uploads/2023/04/Beaconsfield2CampusCatholicValues-930x635.jpg)"></div>
    </div>
<!-- end content block h/h -->

<!-- content_block -->
<div class="c_block white centre" data-anchor="vision" data-float-col="dark">
    <div class="wrapper">
    	        <h1 class="blue">I am the way, the truth and the life.</h1>
        <h4 class="blue">John 14:6</h4>        <p>At St Francis Xavier College we value respect, curiosity, gratitude and hope. We aim to help all students become the best possible version of themselves by providing quality education in a caring yet challenging environment that extends beyond academic excellence. As a leading catholic school in Melbourne, we aim to instil strong character in students from the moment they arrive that will last long after they graduate.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<table width="100%" cellspacing="20" cellpadding="5">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="width: 33%;">
<h2>Spirit of Reconciliation</h2>
<p>St Francis Xavier College acknowledges Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples as Australia’s First People and Traditional Custodians. We are proud and fortunate to live and serve on the land of the Bunurong people. We recognise their intelligence, care and stewardship of this land for many generations. We pay respect to their elders, past, present and emerging. We commit ourselves to moving forward in a spirit of reconciliation.</p>
</td>
<td style="width: 33%;">
<h2>Unconditional Respect</h2>
<p>St Francis Xavier College acknowledges the dignity and value of every person, believing that we are made in the image of God. We are committed to embracing diversity and eliminating systems, practices and beliefs that exclude, divide or disadvantage people. St Francis Xavier College welcomes people of all ability, colour, culture, faith, financial circumstance, gender identity and sexual orientation.</p>
</td>
<td style="width: 33%;">
<h2>Safe School Culture</h2>
<p>St Francis Xavier College is committed to creating a child safe community. We work proactively to prevent any form of abuse or bullying and will respond with compassion and care if concerns are raised. We intentionally build a culture which promotes the safety and wellbeing of all members of our community.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
    </div>
</div>
